.SUBCKT LM2576_SIMPLE 1 2 3 4 5
* Pinout: 1=VIN 2=OUT 3=GND 4=FB 5=ON_OFF
* This is a simplified behavioral model for educational simulation
* It switches VIN to OUT whenever Feedback (Pin 4) drops below 1.23V

* The Voltage Controlled Switch (The transistor inside)
S_Switch 1 2 CTRL 0 POWER_SW

* The Logic (Comparator)
* If V(FB) < 1.23V, Output 10V to Gate. Otherwise 0V.
B_Logic CTRL 0 V = V(4) < 15.0 ? 10 : 0

* Switch Physics (0.2 Ohm resistance when ON)
.MODEL POWER_SW SW(Ron=0.2 Roff=100Meg Vt=5)
.ENDS
